    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-05T04:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-05T04:54:00-05:00" n="689"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.6363/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-05T13:00:00+03:06"
                            >June 5, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 7—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Referring to cable May 19<note n="35" xml:id="d689fn35">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> and despatch May 22 from Cairo.<note
                        n="36" xml:id="d689fn36">No. 10, not printed.</note> Should Department
                    discuss with Ohliger problem of defense and denial operations at Dhahran, sight
                    should not be lost of desirability of utilizing American military forces if
                    needed and practicable and of protecting insofar as possible oil concession
                    rights and oil company personnel by inducting active American participants into
                    United States Army and by giving timely notice to Saudi Government through this
                    Legation of Army’s intentions.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
